# Tests

## Commands

- Unit/component: `task test` or `npm test`
- Extension host: `task test-extension` or `npm run test:extension`

## Jest (default)

- Config: [`jest.config.js`](jest.config.js). Roots: `src/` and `webview-ui/`.
- **`vscode` is mocked**: `moduleNameMapper` maps `vscode` → [`src/test/vscodeMock.ts`](src/test/vscodeMock.ts). Extend the mock instead of ad-hoc `jest.mock("vscode")` per file when possible.
- **`src/test/suite/` is excluded** from Jest (`testPathIgnorePatterns`)—those tests run under Mocha in the extension host.

## Extension-host tests (`@vscode/test-electron`)

- Runner: [`src/test/runExtensionTests.ts`](src/test/runExtensionTests.ts) → [`src/test/suite/index`](src/test/suite/).
- Use when you need the real Extension Host API (activation, webviews, commands). Expect headless/display constraints on Linux CI.

## Placement rule of thumb

| Change | Prefer |
| --- | --- |
| Service logic, parsers, pure helpers | Jest under `src/**/*.test.ts` |
| React components | Jest + Testing Library under `webview-ui/**/*.test.tsx` |
| Extension activation, real webview, integration | `src/test/suite/` |
